By Deji Elumoye President Muhammadu Buhari has condoled with the family, friends, government and people of Katsina state on the death of Abdullahi Dikko Inde, the immediate past Comptroller General of the Nigeria Customs Service (NCS). The President, in a statement on Friday by his Media Assistant, Garba Shehu, took note of his past services to the nation, and prayed to Allah to accept the good deeds and forgive the sins of the deceased and grant his family the fortitude to bear the loss.